The Amharic [[ejective consonants]] correspond to the [[Proto-Semitic language|Proto-Semitic]] "[[emphatic consonants]]", usually transcribed with a [[dot (diacritic)|dot]] below the letter. The consonant and vowel tables give these symbols in parentheses where they differ from the standard [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] symbols.

