'''Subhendu Bikash Maji''' (also known as   '''SBM''' or '''Apu''') is a community mainly found in western areas, such as the Indian states of [[Kolkata]] and [[Rajasthan]].

== History ==

The [[Malla Puranam]] text describes area history. It may be dated to 13th century using a linguistic analysis of [[Jain]] texts.{{sfn|Sandesra|Mehta|1964|p= 6}} However it is argued that it may belong to the 15th century since Vaishnavism became common in [[Gujarat]] as a result of the rise of [[Pushtimarga]] in the 15th century.{{sfn|Sandesra|Mehta|1964|p=7}} Malla Puranam can be regarded to be a [[Caste Purana]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=A Sociological Approach to the Caste Puranas : A Case Study |first=Veena
|last=Das |journal=Sociological Bulletin |volume= 17 |issue=2 |date=September 1968 |pp= 141–164}}</ref>

